article.description: Erica McCall scored 18 points and No. 11 Stanford crushed Chattanooga 73-30 on Monday night.
article.headline: No. 11 Stanford women crush Chattanooga 73-30
article.story:
STANFORD, Calif. --  Erica McCall scored 18 points and No. 11 Stanford crushed Chattanooga 73-30 on Monday night.

McCall was 9 of 16 from the floor, scoring from the inside with ease, and added eight rebounds for the Cardinal (10-2). Lili Thompson scored 11 points and Karlie Samuelson had 10 points. Stanford outrebounded the Lady Mocs 48-40, had 11 steals and eight blocked shots.

Chattanooga shot just over 21 percent and made 4 of 17 3-point attempts. The Mocs went to the foul line just twice in the game and committed 21 turnovers.

Alicia Payne led Chattanooga (8-5) with nine points and seven rebounds, and Keiana Gilbert grabbed nine rebounds. Chattanooga did not score in double digits in any of the four quarters -- with a low of five points in the fourth.

Stanford closed the first half with an 11-2 run -- as Chattanooga went 6:43 without scoring -- and led 40-18 at the break.
